{{one source|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox serial killer |name=Václav Mrázek |image= |caption= |alt= |birthname=Václav Mrázek |alias= |birth_date={{Birth date and age|1925|10|22}} |birth_place= [[Svinařov]], [[Czechoslovakia]], now [[Czech Republic]] |death_date={{Death date and age|1957|12|29|1925|10|22|df=y}} |death_place= [[Pankrác Prison]], [[Prague]], Czechoslovakia, now Czech Republic |cause= Executed |conviction= |sentence= |victims=7 |beginyear= |endyear= |country=Czechoslovakia |states= |apprehended=March 1957 |signature=Václav Mrázek signature.jpg }} '''Václav Mrázek''' (October 22, 1925 &ndash; December 29, 1957<ref>[https://zpravy.idnes.cz/foto.aspx?r=krimi&c=A171215_123038_krimi_iri&foto=IRI7003c0_DSC09263.JPG Protocol of execution]</ref> in [[Prague]]) was a [[Czechs|Czech]] [[serial killer]] who was convicted of murdering seven people. Six of his victims were women, and one was a man. His murders (or attempted murders) were primarily sexually motivated, although he also burgled his victims' homes. Besides murders, he was convicted of 127 other [[crime]]s.
Despite being searched for in relation to the murders in the [[Chomutov]] region (where he committed most of his crimes), he evaded capture for a long time. He was convicted and [[death penalty|sentenced to death]] in 1957, the same year he was captured and he was executed on December 29, 1957 in [[Pankrác Prison]].
== Childhood == Václav Mrázek was born in a small village of [[Svinařov]] as one of 12 children. His father was a [[miner]], who was also a binge drinker and used to [[Physical abuse|beat]] both his wife and the children. Often hungry at home, Mrázek started stealing from an early age, encouraged by his mother.
== Capture == Mrázek was caught in March 1957 during a house inspection following a theft in the [[Libušín]] mine, where he was working as a spa staff attendant.
