{{Infobox serial killer | name = Louay Omar Mohammed al-Taei | image = | caption = | alt = | birthname = Louay Omar Mohammed al-Taei | alias = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Iraq]] | death_date = | death_place = | cause = | conviction = | sentence = | victims = 43 | beginyear = October 2005 | endyear = March 2006 | country = [[Iraq]] | states = [[Kirkuk]] | apprehended = March 2006 }} '''Dr. Louay Omar Mohammed al-Taei''' is an Iraqi [[medical doctor]] accused of murdering wounded [[policemen]], [[soldiers]] and [[officials]] in [[Kirkuk]] while pretending to treat them.
According to police, Louay administered [[anti-coagulant]]s to pro-Coalition forces brought into the hospital for treatment, to excaberate their bleeding and causing a number of deaths.<ref name="indy">[[The Independent]], [http://news.independent.co.uk/world/middle_east/article353015.ece Insurgent doctor killed dozens of wounded soldiers] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060421161816/http://news.independent.co.uk/world/middle_east/article353015.ece |date=2006-04-21 }}, 23 March 2006</ref> A police investigation revealed that he had killed 43 people from October 2005 to March 2006.<ref name="GU">{{cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2006/apr/17/iraq.topstories3 | title='I made a mixture of drugs and injected them. They were dead in three hours' | publisher=The Guardian | date=April 16, 2006 | accessdate=28 March 2014 | author=Howard, Michael}}</ref> He claimed to be recruited into [[Jamaat Ansar al-Sunna]] in August 2005.<ref name="GU"/>
He was arrested after [[Malla Yassin]] was arrested in early 2006, and confessed to being the leader of an [[Iraqi insurgency (Iraq War)|insurgent cell]] that included Louay.<ref name="indy"/>
