{{Infobox serial killer |name=Johannes Mashiane |image= |image_size= |caption= |birthname=Johannes Mashiane |alias=The Beast of Atteridgeville |birth_date= |birth_place=[[South Africa]] |death_date=October 1989 |death_place=[[Marabastad, Pretoria|Marabastad]], [[Pretoria]], [[South Africa]] |cause=[[Suicide]] |victims=13 |country=[[South Africa]] |states=[[Pretoria]] |beginyear=1982 |endyear=1989 |apprehended= |penalty= }}
'''Johannes Mashiane''', nicknamed '''The Beast of [[Atteridgeville]]''', was a [[South Africa]]n rapist and [[serial killer]] who was responsible for the deaths of 13 victims before committing suicide in 1989. Mashiane was being chased by police in the [[Pretoria]] suburb of [[Marabastad, Pretoria|Marabastad]] when he jumped underneath a bus.
Mashiane started his murderous activity in 1977 by killing his girlfriend. He was sentenced to five years' imprisonment and was released in 1982.<ref name="Madness">{{Cite web |url=http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |title=‘‘A History of Madness’’ : Serial Killers. |access-date=2010-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003172900/http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |archive-date=2011-10-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> After being released, he immediately started his spate of [[murder]] and [[sodomy]], accounting for the deaths of at least 12 young boys by [[strangulation]] or [[stoning]]. One victim is known to have survived Mashiane's attention.<ref name="Survivor">[http://www.francesfarmersrevenge.com/stuff/serialkillers/mashiane.htm ‘‘Frances Farmers Revenge’’ : Johannes Mashiane.]</ref>
