{{Infobox serial killer |name=Jack Mogale |image= |image_size= |caption= |birthname=Jack Mogale |alias=West-End Serial Killer |birth_date= September 1968 |birth_place= {{ZAF}} |death_date= |death_place= |cause= |conviction=Murder, kidnapping, rape |sentence= Life imprisonment |victims=16 |country=South Africa |states= |beginyear=2008 |endyear=2009 |apprehended=2009 }}
{{Wikinews|South African serial killer guilty of nineteen rapes, sixteen murders}} '''Jack Mogale''' (born 1968/9), dubbed the '''West-End Serial Killer''' by police, is a South African [[serial killer]] who killed 16 people in 2008 and 2009. On 17 February 2011, Mogale was convicted on 52 of 61 charges related to 16 murders, 19 rapes, and 9 kidnappings.<ref name="Verdict">{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316. |title=''News 24'' : West-End killer awaits sentencing. |access-date=2011-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629051305/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316. |archive-date=2011-06-29 |url-status=dead }}</ref>
Mogale committed his crimes near his residence in [[Westonaria]] and [[Lenasia]], south of [[Johannesburg]]. Two women who survived being attacked by him testified at trial that he had claimed to be a [[Zion Christian Church]] (ZCC) preacher and a prophet.<ref name="Verdict" />
